 aren\u2019t just top-notch, they\u2019re often top-secret. A team of bold thinkers committed to exploring what\u2019s next. Opportunities to gain new knowledge - as it\u2019s discovered. Strong background with deploying and maintaining RedHat Linux/CentOS Client/Server environments. Experience with implementing Linux security controls to maintain system compliance. Familiarity with compliance controls: STIGs (Security Technical Implementation Guides), RMF (Risk Management Framework), DFARS (Defense Federal Acquisition Regulation Supplement), NIST SP 800-171, Cybersecurity Maturity Model Certification (CMMC), CIS ControlsFamiliarity supporting software/hardware development tools & processes: JIRA, GitLab, Jenkins, CI/CD, GIT, DevOps, Software Development Kits (SDK)s, IDEs. Scripting languages such as Bash, Python, Ruby, PowerShell. Experience installing, configuring, and writing ansible playbooks for infrastructure as code (IaC) automation with production and development environments. Kickstart/PXE Boot used to automate installation of operating system. Monitoring and alerting packages such as Nagios and Ganglia. TCP/IP, Internet Routing Protocols, private and public networks, VLANs, Firewalls, Load Balancers, addressing schemes, subnet creation and subnet masking. Experience with patching of Windows platforms Client 10 and Server 2012R2/2016 or newer. Experience with patching of RedHat Linux/CentOS. Experience managing virtual machine with VMware vSphere and related technologies. Creative thinking with the ability to multi-task. Team player who thrives in collaborative environments and revels in team success. Commitment to ongoing professional development. Additional Information: Upon offer of employment, the individual will be subject to a background check and a drug screen. Aleron companies (Acara Solutions, Aleron Shared Resources, Broadleaf Results, Lume Strategies, TalentRise, Viaduct, and Aleron?s strategic partner, SDI) are Equal Employment Opportunity and A